# 🤖 Autonomous Line Tracking with Obstacle Avoidance
### Complete Presentation Document — TurtleBot3 Waffle Pi · ROS2 · Hybrid APF + State Machine

---

## Slide 1 — Title

> **Project:** Autonomous Line Tracking with Obstacle Avoidance  
> **Approach:** Hybrid APF (Artificial Potential Fields) + State Machine Controller  
> **Platform:** TurtleBot3 Waffle Pi · ROS2 · Python 3  
> **Presented by:** Aashish · April 2026  

---

## Slide 2 — Introduction

- A **self-driving robot** that follows a yellow line on the floor — like a car staying in its lane
- Uses a **Pi Camera** for line vision and a **360° LiDAR** for obstacle sensing
- Built on **ROS2** — the industry standard for modern robotics
- Runs a **Hybrid Controller**: smooth APF steering + reliable state machine for decisions
- The robot **never fully stops** — maintains a minimum 0.04 m/s at all times

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    CAM["📷 Camera\n/image_raw"] --> BRAIN["🧠 Brain\nline_tracking.py\n20 Hz"]
    LIDAR["📡 LiDAR\n/scan"] --> BRAIN
    ODOM["📍 Odometry\n/odom"] --> BRAIN
    BRAIN --> CMD["🤖 Robot\n/cmd_vel"]
    BRAIN --> RVIZ["📊 RViz2\nVisualization"]
```

