## Slide 4 — Problem Statement

**The Challenge:**
- Robot must follow a colored line **smoothly** — not jerk or oscillate
- Real environments have **unexpected obstacles** blocking the path
- Must **navigate around** them and **re-find the line** automatically

**Why naive solutions fail:**

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Robot
    participant V as Velocity

    Note over R,V: FOLLOWING_LINE
    R->>V: vx=0.15, wz=proportional

    Note over R,V: ⚠️ Obstacle detected!
    R->>V: vx=0.0, wz=0.0 (FULL STOP)
    Note right of V: 💥 Jerk #1

    Note over R,V: EVADING
    R->>V: vx=0.05, wz=-0.50 (hard spin)
    Note right of V: 💥 Jerk #2

    Note over R,V: CLEARING
    R->>V: vx=0.12, wz=0.0 (dead straight)
    Note right of V: 💥 Jerk #3

    Note over R,V: ARC_RECOVERY
    R->>V: vx=0.10, wz=+0.45 (fixed arc)
    Note right of V: 💥 Jerk #4
```

> Each state transition is an **instantaneous velocity jump** causing wheel slip, physical jerking, and unstable sensor readings.

---

## Slide 5 — Objectives

- ✅ **Detect** a yellow line reliably using a camera under real lighting conditions
- ✅ **Follow** the line smoothly using proportional APF (magnetic-force) steering
- ✅ **Detect obstacles** using LiDAR with a graduated 3-zone proximity system
- ✅ **Bypass obstacles** using the obstacle's measured geometry (width + distance)
- ✅ **Recover and re-acquire** the line automatically after every obstacle

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["🎯 Detect\nYellow Line"] --> B["🚗 Follow\nAPF Steering"]
    B --> C["📡 Sense\nObstacle Zones"]
    C --> D["🔄 Bypass\nSinusoidal Path"]
    D --> E["🔍 Recover\nLine Re-Acquisition"]
    E --> B
```

---

## Slide 6 — System Architecture

### Sensor → Brain → Robot Pipeline

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Sensors["🔌 Sensor Layer"]
        CAM["📷 Pi Camera\n640×480\n/camera/image_raw"]
        LIDAR["📡 LiDAR\n360° scan\n/scan"]
        ODOM["📍 Odometry\npose + heading\n/odom"]
    end

    subgraph Brain["🧠 Controller (20 Hz)"]
        DETECT["Line Detection\nHSV Masking + Contours"]
        APF["APF Steering\nProportional Error"]
        OBS["Obstacle Modelling\nRANSAC + SVD"]
        SM["State Machine\n4 States"]
    end

    subgraph Output["📤 Output Layer"]
        CMD["/cmd_vel\nTwist messages"]
        VIZ["/visualization_marker_array\nRViz2 Forces"]
    end

    CAM --> DETECT
    LIDAR --> OBS
    ODOM --> SM
    DETECT --> APF
    APF --> SM
    OBS --> SM
    SM --> CMD
    SM --> VIZ
```

> **Key fact:** The controller runs at **20 Hz** (every 50 ms), fusing all three sensor streams into a single velocity command.

---

## Slide 7 — Line Detection (Vision Pipeline)

**Step-by-step:**

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["📷 Raw Frame\n640×480"] --> B["Resize\n320×240\nINTER_NEAREST"]
    B --> C["BGR → HSV\nColour Space"]
    C --> D["Yellow Mask\nH:15-42\nS:70-255\nV:70-255"]
    D --> E["Morphological\nOpen + Close\n3×3 kernel"]
    E --> F["Find Contours\ncv2.findContours"]
    F --> G{"Area\n> 200 px²?"}
    G -- Yes --> H["Compute Centroid\nM10/M00, M01/M00"]
    G -- No --> I["Return None\nLine Lost"]
    H --> J["line_cx\n= pixel position"]
```

**HSV Yellow Range (Pi Camera V2 + libcamera):**

| Channel | Low | High |
|:---|:---|:---|
| Hue (H) | 15 | 42 |
| Saturation (S) | 70 | 255 |
| Value (V) | 70 | 255 |

> **Debug tip:** A log every 3 s reports `yellow_px` and `best_area` — if both are 0 under good lighting, the HSV range needs re-tuning.

---

## Slide 8 — APF Steering (Line Following)

> **Philosophy:** The yellow line acts as a *magnetic opposite pole* — it **attracts** the robot proportionally to how far off-centre it is.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph APF["Artificial Potential Field"]
        E["Error (px)\n= line_cx − 160"] --> W["Turn Rate\nwz = −k_att × error\ncapped ±1.2 rad/s"]
        W --> V["Forward Speed\nvx = follow_speed\n× (1 − 0.4|wz|/1.2)"]
        V --> MIN["Min Speed\nvx = max(0.04, vx)"]
    end
    MIN --> CMD["/cmd_vel"]
```

**Key parameters:**

| Parameter | Default | Effect |
|:---|:---|:---|
| `k_att` | 0.010 | Steering gain: px → rad/s |
| `follow_speed` | 0.15 m/s | Forward speed on straight |
| `min_speed` | 0.04 m/s | Never stops completely |

**Lost line behaviour:** Robot rotates toward `last_error` direction at `min_speed` to search.

---

## Slide 9 — Obstacle Detection — 3-Zone System

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    SCAN["📡 LiDAR /scan\n360 ranges"] --> CONE["Extract Front Cone\nindices 0-20 and 340-360\n(±20° around forward)"]
    CONE --> MIN["front_dist\n= min of clean cone"]
    MIN --> Z1{"< 1.00 m\nZone 1?"}
    Z1 -- No --> FOLLOW["Continue\nFOLLOWING_LINE"]
    Z1 -- Yes --> LOG["🟡 Log: Obstacle Aware"]
    LOG --> Z2{"< 0.75 m\nZone 2?"}
    Z2 -- No --> MEAS["Measure Box\nRANSAC + SVD"]
    Z2 -- Yes --> BYPASS["🟠 → BYPASSING"]
    MIN --> Z3{"< 0.30 m\nZone 3?"}
    Z3 -- Yes --> STOP["🔴 HARD_STOP\nImmediate halt"]
```

**Zone Summary:**

| Zone | Threshold | Action |
|:---|:---|:---|
| 🟡 Zone 1 — Awareness | < 1.00 m | Log warning, keep following |
| 🟠 Zone 2 — Bypass | < 0.75 m | Trigger sinusoidal bypass |
| 🔴 Zone 3 — Hard Stop | < 0.30 m | `vx=0, wz=0` immediately |

---

## Slide 10 — Smart Obstacle Bypass (RANSAC + SVD)

**Obstacle width measurement algorithm:**

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    PTS["LiDAR points\nin front cone"] --> CART["Convert to\nCartesian XY"]
    CART --> RANSAC["RANSAC\nRemove outliers\n40 iterations\nthresh=0.015m"]
    RANSAC --> SVD["SVD\nFind dominant\nface direction"]
    SVD --> PROJ["Project onto\nface direction\nwidth = max−min"]
    PROJ --> OUT["Output:\nwidth (m)\ndistance (m)\nface_angle (rad)"]
```

**Bypass path calculation:**

```
Required clearance angle:
  θ = atan2(width/2 + 0.30m, distance)

Sinusoidal amplitude:
  A = θ × π / bypass_duration

Steering command (progress 0→1):
  wz = −A × sin(progress × 2π)
  vx = bypass_speed × (1 − 0.3|wz|/A)
```

> The bypass traces a smooth **S-curve**: steer right → straighten → steer left — returning the robot to the line.

---

## Slide 11 — State Machine (Current Implementation)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> FOLLOWING_LINE : Node Start

    state FOLLOWING_LINE {
        direction LR
        APF : Proportional Steering (k_att=0.010)
        Zones : 3-Zone LiDAR Watch
    }

    FOLLOWING_LINE --> BYPASSING : front_dist < 0.75m (Zone 2)
    FOLLOWING_LINE --> HARD_STOP : front_dist < 0.30m (Zone 3)

    state BYPASSING {
        direction LR
        SineCurve : wz = -A·sin(2π·t/T)
        GeoAmp : Amplitude from RANSAC+SVD
        Watch : Camera + watchdog
    }

    state HARD_STOP {
        Halt : vx=0 wz=0
    }

    state STUCK {
        Reverse : vx = -0.10 m/s for 1.5s
    }

    BYPASSING --> FOLLOWING_LINE : Line found (area > 3000px, path clear)
    BYPASSING --> STUCK : Timeout > 12s
    HARD_STOP --> FOLLOWING_LINE : front_dist > 0.35m (hysteresis)
    STUCK --> BYPASSING : Reverse complete
```

**State behaviours:**

| State | Speed | Turn | Exit Condition |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| FOLLOWING_LINE | 0.15 m/s | Proportional APF | obstacle < 0.75m |
| BYPASSING | 0.10 m/s | Sinusoidal S-curve | line found OR timeout |
| HARD_STOP | 0 m/s | 0 rad/s | obstacle > 0.35m |
| STUCK | -0.10 m/s | 0 rad/s | 1.5s elapsed |

---

## Slide 12 — Smooth Avoidance: Evolution of the Design

**Three design options were evaluated:**

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph OptionA["Option A: Velocity Ramping (Easy)"]
        direction LR
        SM_A["State Machine\nunchanged"] --> EMA["EMA Filter\nα = 0.15"] --> CMD_A["/cmd_vel\nsmoothed"]
    end

    subgraph OptionB["Option B: Curved Bypass (Chosen ✅)"]
        direction LR
        C1["BYPASSING\nwz = -A·sin(2π·t/T)"]
    end

    subgraph OptionC["Option C: Full APF Blending (Best smoothness)"]
        direction LR
        ATT["F_att\nLine pull"] --> BLEND["Σ wz"]
        REP["F_rep\nObstacle push"] --> BLEND
        BLEND --> CMD_C["/cmd_vel\ncontinuous"]
    end
```

**Comparison:**

| Feature | Option A: Ramping | Option B: Curved Bypass ✅ | Option C: Full APF |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| **Difficulty** | Easy | Moderate | Hard |
| **Smoothness** | Good | Excellent | Best |
| **Keeps State Machine?** | ✅ Yes | Partially | ❌ No |
| **Chosen?** | Quick win | **✅ Implemented** | Future work |

> **Option B was implemented** — replacing the old 3-phase EVADE→CLEAR→ARC_RECOVERY with a single continuous sinusoidal BYPASSING state.

