## Slide 14 — Deployment Guide

### How to Run the System

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant L as 💻 Laptop
    participant P as 🍓 Raspberry Pi

    L->>P: rsync / scp waffle_pi_lane_tracking/
    Note over P: Step 1: Copy code to Pi

    P->>P: Terminal 1: ros2 launch turtlebot3_bringup robot.launch.py
    Note over P: Step 2: Start robot drivers

    P->>P: Terminal 2: ros2 run camera_ros camera_node
    Note over P: Step 3: Start camera (RGB888)

    P->>P: Terminal 3: colcon build → source → ros2 launch
    Note over P: Step 4: Build & run brain

    L->>L: Terminal 4: ros2 launch ... rviz:=true
    Note over L: Step 5: View visualization
```

**Quick-start commands:**

```bash
# Pi — Terminal 1: Drivers
ros2 launch turtlebot3_bringup robot.launch.py

# Pi — Terminal 2: Camera (RGB888 fixes NV21 colour decode)
ros2 run camera_ros camera_node --ros-args \
  -p width:=640 -p height:=480 -p pixel_format:=RGB888

# Pi — Terminal 3: Build & Launch Brain
cd ~/Desktop/ROS2_workspace
colcon build --packages-select waffle_pi_lane_tracking
source install/setup.bash
ros2 launch waffle_pi_lane_tracking line_tracking.launch.py enable_rviz:=true

# Laptop — Terminal 4: RViz Visualization
ros2 launch waffle_pi_lane_tracking line_tracking.launch.py rviz:=true
```

> 💡 **Tune magnetic pull strength:** append `k_att:=0.005` or `k_att:=0.015` to Terminal 3

**Verify the system is running:**

```bash
ros2 node list | grep line_tracking    # → /line_tracking_controller
ros2 topic echo /cmd_vel --once        # → should show velocity commands
```

