## Slide 15 — Results & Advantages / Limitations

### Results Achieved

- ✅ Yellow line tracking at **0.15 m/s** with smooth proportional corrections
- ✅ Obstacles detected and geometrically measured from up to **1 metre**
- ✅ Sinusoidal bypass completed in **~6 seconds** with geometric precision
- ✅ Line re-acquired automatically — **zero human intervention**
- ✅ Minimum **0.04 m/s** maintained across all states (never stops)
- ✅ Live RViz2 visualization: 🔵 line-pull · 🔴 obstacle-push · 🟢 resultant

### Advantages vs Limitations

| Advantages ✅ | Limitations ⚠️ |
|:---|:---|
| Geometry-driven bypass (RANSAC+SVD) | Yellow line only (fixed HSV range) |
| Smooth sinusoidal motion — no jerking | Sensitive to sunlight and shadows |
| Fully tunable at launch (no recompile) | SVD best for flat box-shaped obstacles |
| Rescue + watchdog for self-recovery | Launch file params partially mismatched |
| Sensor fusion: Camera + LiDAR + Odom | Single camera — no depth data |

